# Android Kiosk Rules

## Context
- This app runs on an unattended public tablet. The public must not be able to escape the app, access system settings, or interact with anything outside the ticket purchase flow.
- Apply when touching navigation, system UI, screen management, or the Android manifest.

## Requirements

### System UI
- `SystemChrome.setEnabledSystemUIMode(SystemUiMode.immersiveSticky)` — called in `main()` before `runApp`. Must not be removed or conditionally disabled.
- `WakelockPlus.enable()` — screen must never sleep while kiosk is running.
- `SystemChrome.setPreferredOrientations([DeviceOrientation.landscapeLeft, DeviceOrientation.landscapeRight])` — landscape only, no accidental portrait.

### Navigation Lock
- `PopScope(canPop: false)` is **mandatory** on `PaymentScreen` and `ConfirmationScreen`.
- The public must not be able to back-navigate away from an in-progress payment.
- After payment (success or failure), flow exits via `context.go(...)` — never `context.pop()`.

### Idle Timeout
- Every feature screen except `AttractScreen` must implement an idle reset timer.
- Default: `AppConfig.idleTimeoutSeconds` (default 60s, configurable via `--dart-define`).
- Timer cancels in `dispose()` — no leak.
- Any user interaction (tap, scroll) resets the timer.
- On timeout: `context.go(KioskRoutes.attract)` — full stack reset.

### Admin Access
- Admin panel accessed by 5-tap gesture on a hidden corner of the `AttractScreen` (top-right 80×80px area), then PIN entry.
- The hidden area has no visual indicator — it is not discoverable by casual users.
- PIN entry uses numeric keyboard only (`TextInputType.number`), `obscureText: true`.
- Failed PIN attempts reset the input silently — no lockout counter shown (to avoid revealing the mechanism).

### Android Manifest
- `android:launchMode="singleTask"` — no duplicate activity stack.
- `android:screenOrientation="sensorLandscape"` — enforced in manifest as well as Dart.
- `HOME` + `DEFAULT` intent categories — app becomes the launcher on Device Owner setup.
- `android:showWhenLocked="true"` + `android:turnScreenOn="true"` — kiosk works from lock screen.
- SumUp Bluetooth permissions declared: `BLUETOOTH`, `BLUETOOTH_SCAN`, `BLUETOOTH_CONNECT`, `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION`.

### Device Owner (Production)
- Full lock-down via Device Owner: `adb shell dpm set-device-owner ee.kaasan.museum_kiosk/.AdminReceiver`
- After enrolment, call `DevicePolicyManager.setLockTaskPackages()` — prevents home/recents escape.
- This step runs on the tablet by an operator — not automated by the app.

## Trust Framework Mapping (thesis §4.3)

This kiosk operates at **L3 autonomy** (Monitored) for AI-assisted development:
- **Observability:** All payment events logged with `orderId`. Every state transition written to DB.
- **Reversibility:** Orders can be voided via admin panel. DB records are append-only audit trail.
- **Blast Radius:** Payment is isolated behind `PaymentService`. Navigation is constrained. Admin is PIN-gated.

## Critical Rules
- NEVER remove `PopScope(canPop: false)` from Payment or Confirmation screens.
- NEVER disable `immersiveSticky` or `WakelockPlus`.
- ALWAYS cancel idle timers in `dispose()`.
- ALWAYS use `context.go()` not `context.pop()` for post-payment navigation.
- ALWAYS gate admin panel with both gesture + PIN.
